Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
load_netlist_i...undefined_cell(25.10)  load_netlist_i...undefined_cell(25.10)

Name
       load_netlist_ignore_undefined_cell

Syntax
       load_netlist_ignore_undefined_cell { 1 | 0 }

       If false, a Verilog reference to an undefined cell (for example, a Ver-
       ilog  module name that has no matching library cell and no Verilog mod-
       ule definition) causes an error and an exit after parsing the  netlist.
       If  true,  an  empty Verilog module is created with a warning.  The de-
       fault value is true in Innovus to allow repair of `dirty netlists'.  An
       empty  module  will  become  an hinst or inst depending on the value of
       setImportMode -keepEmptyModule.

       To set this variable, use the set command.

       Datatype: boolean

       Default: 1

